*_»\"><span class=\"name\">Matrix</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_ᵥ*_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`v ᵥ* M` (notation for `vecMul v M`) is the vector-matrix product of vector `v` and matrix `M`,\nwhere `v` is seen as a row vector.\nPut another way, `v ᵥ* M` is the vector whose entries are those of `row v * M` (see `row_vecMul`).\n\nThe notation has precedence 73, which comes immediately before ` ⬝ᵥ ` for `dotProduct`,\nso that `v ᵥ* A ⬝ᵥ w ᵥ* B` is parsed as `(v ᵥ* A) ⬝ᵥ (w ᵥ* B)`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Matrix/Mul.html#Matrix.«term_ᵥ*_»","kind":"def","line":716,"name":"Matrix.«term_ᵥ*_»","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Data/Matrix/Mul.lean#L716-L717"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Matrix/Mul.html#Matrix.vecMul\"><span class=\"name\">Matrix</span>.<span class=\"name\">vecMul</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">m</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">n</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_3}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#NonUnitalNonAssocSemiring\">NonUnitalNonAssocSemiring</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Fintype/Defs.html#Fintype\">Fintype</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">v</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">m</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">M</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/LinearAlgebra/Matrix/Defs.html#Matrix\">Matrix</a> <span class=\"fn\">m</span> <span class=\"fn\">n</span> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">n</span> → <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`v ᵥ* M` (notation for `vecMul v M`) is the vector-matrix product of vector `v` and matrix `M`,\nwhere `v` is seen as a row vector.\nPut another way, `v ᵥ* M` is the vector whose entries are those of `row v * M` (see `row_vecMul`).\n\nThe notation has precedence 73, which comes immediately before ` ⬝ᵥ ` for `dotProduct`,\nso that `v ᵥ* A ⬝ᵥ w ᵥ* B` is parsed as `(v ᵥ* A) ⬝ᵥ (w ᵥ* B)`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Matrix/Mul.html#Matrix.vecMul","kind":"def","line":705,"name":"Matrix.vecMul","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Data/Matrix/Mul.lean#L705-L714"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Matrix/Mul.html#Matrix.«term_*ᵥ_»\"><span class=\"name\">Matrix</span>.<span class=\"name\">«term_*ᵥ_»</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.TrailingParserDescr\">Lean.TrailingParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`M *ᵥ v` (notation for `mulVec M v`) is the matrix-vector product of matrix `M` and vector `v`,\nwhere `v` is 